.fi
.PP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Render escaped \fCexpr\fP\&. This is the default framework behavior\&. The \fC| esc\fP suffix is only necessary if \fCESCAPE\fP global variable is set to \fCFALSE\fP\&.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.nf
{{ string expr, arg1, \&.\&.\&., argN | format }}
.fi
.PP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Render an ICU-formatted \fCexpr\fP and pass the comma-separated arguments, where \fCarg1, \&.\&.\&., argn\fP is one of:- \fC'date'\fP, \fC'time'\fP, \fC'number, integer'\fP, \fC'number, currency'\fP, or \fC'number, percent'\fP\&.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.nf
<include
    [ if="{{ bool condition }}" ]
    href="{{ string subtemplate }}"
/>
.fi
.PP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Get contents of \fCsubtemplate\fP and insert at current position in template if optional condition is \fCTRUE\fP\&.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.nf
<exclude>text-block</exclude>
.fi
.PP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Remove \fCtext-block\fP at runtime\&. Used for embedding comments in templates\&.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.nf
<ignore>text-block</ignore>
.fi
.PP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Display \fCtext-block\fP as-is, without interpretation/modification by the template engine\&.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.nf
<check if="{{ bool condition }}">
    <true>true-block</true>
    <false>false-block</false>
</check>
.fi
.PP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Evaluate condition\&. If \fCTRUE\fP, then \fCtrue-block\fP is rendered\&. Otherwise, \fCfalse-block\fP is used\&.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.nf
<loop
    from="{{ statement }}"
    to="{{ bool expr }}"
    [ step="{{ statement }}" ]>
    text-block
</loop>
.fi
.PP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Evaluate \fCfrom\fP statement once\&. Check if the expression in the \fCto\fP attribute is \fCTRUE\fP, render \fCtext-block\fP and evaluate \fCstep\fP statement\&. Repeat iteration until \fCto\fP expression is \fCFALSE\fP\&.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.nf
<repeat
    group="{{ array @group|expr }}"
    [ key="{{ scalar @key }}" ]
    value="{{ mixed @value }}
    [ counter="{{ scalar @key }}" ]>
    text-block
</repeat>
.fi
.PP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Repeat \fCtext-block\fP as many times as there are elements in the array variable \fC@group\fP or the expression \fCexpr\fP\&. \fC@key\fP and \fC@value\fP function in the same manner as the key-value pair in the equivalent PHP \fCforeach()\fP statement\&. Variable represented by \fCkey\fP in \fCcounter\fP attribute increments by \fC1\fP with every iteration\&.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.nf
<switch expr="{{ scalar expr }}">
    <case value="{{ scalar @value|expr }}" break="{{ bool TRUE|FALSE }}">
        text-block
    </case>
    \&.
    \&.
    \&.
</switch>
.fi
.PP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Equivalent of the PHP switch-case jump table structure\&.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.nf
{* text-block *}
.fi
.PP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Alias for \fC<exclude>\fP\&.
.PP
